# Concepts:

	# Pod(Container):
		- Is the smallest unit of the kubernets world;
		- Runs a cointeiner;
		
	# Proxy/Config
	
	# Worker Node:
		- Worler Nodes Run the containers of yours application;
		- "Nodes" ara your machines/ virtual instances;
		- Can have more than one pod;
		
	# Master Node:
		- The control Plane;
		- Control your deployment;
		
	# Cluster
		
				
				
	# Service:
		Exposes Pods to the Cluster or Externally;
		Services group Pods with a shared IP;
		Without services, Pods are very hard to reach and communication is difficult;
		Reaching a Pod from outside the Cluster is not possible at all without Services;